subsubsection ‹Algebraic Properties›

text ‹Here we construct two inner transformations from ‹a ⦂ T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P› to ‹a ⦂ T› and another reversely.
  It is essentially an identity transformation from ‹a› to ‹a› itself.
  The constraints checks 1. if the identity transformation is supported (a very weak requirement),
        2. the container is always non-empty so that an independent assertion ‹P› bound at the element
           type is valid globally (this is a necessary condition).  ›

lemma φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃_Homo[φreason_template name Fa.φsubj [assertion_simps]]:
  ‹ Functional_Transformation_Functor Fa Fa (T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P) T D R pm fm
⟹ Functional_Transformation_Functor Fa Fa T (T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P) D R pm fm
⟹ 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 (∀a. a ∈ D x ⟶ a ∈ R x) ∧ (fm (λx. x) (λ_. P) x = x ∧ pm (λx. x) (λ_. P) x = P)
⟹ (x ⦂ Fa (T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P)) = (x ⦂ Fa T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P)›
  unfolding Functional_Transformation_Functor_def Transformation_def atomize_eq Premise_def BI_eq_iff
  apply (clarsimp; rule)
  subgoal premises prems for p
    by (insert prems(1)[THEN spec[where x=x], THEN spec[where x=‹λx. x›], THEN spec[where x=‹λ_. P›]]
               prems(3-),
        clarsimp)
  subgoal premises prems for p
    by (insert prems(2)[THEN spec[where x=x], THEN spec[where x=‹λx. x›], THEN spec[where x=‹λ_. P›]]
               prems(3-),
        clarsimp) .

lemma φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃_Homo_ty[φreason_template name Fa.φsubj_ty [assertion_simps]]:
  ‹ Functional_Transformation_Functor Fa Fa (T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P) T D R pm fm
⟹ Functional_Transformation_Functor Fa Fa T (T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P) D R pm fm
⟹ 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 (∀a x. a ∈ D x ⟶ a ∈ R x) ∧ (∀x. fm (λx. x) (λ_. P) x = x ∧ pm (λx. x) (λ_. P) x = P)
⟹ Fa (T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P) = (Fa T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P)›
  unfolding Functional_Transformation_Functor_def atomize_eq Premise_def BI_eq_iff
  apply (rule φType_eqI_Tr; clarsimp simp add: Transformation_def)
  subgoal premises prems for x v
    by (insert prems(1)[THEN spec[where x=x], THEN spec[where x=‹λx. x›], THEN spec[where x=‹λ_. P›]]
               prems(3-),
        clarsimp,
        blast)
  subgoal premises prems for x v
    by (insert prems(2)[THEN spec[where x=x], THEN spec[where x=‹λx. x›], THEN spec[where x=‹λ_. P›]]
               prems(3-),
        clarsimp) .

subsection ‹Dependent Sum Type›

φtype_def φDependent_Sum :: ‹('c ⇒ ('a,'b) φ) ⇒ ('a, 'c × 'b) φ› ("Σ")
  where ‹cx ⦂ Σ T ≡ (snd cx) ⦂ T (fst cx)›
  deriving Basic
    and ‹ (⋀A. Object_Equiv (T A) (eq A))
      ⟹ Object_Equiv (Σ T) (λx y. fst y = fst x ∧ eq (fst x) (snd x) (snd y))›
    and ‹(⋀A. Abstract_Domain (T A) (P A)) ⟹ Abstract_Domain (Σ T) (λx. P (fst x) (snd x))›
    and ‹(⋀A. Abstract_Domain⇩L (T A) (P A)) ⟹ Abstract_Domain⇩L (Σ T) (λx. P (fst x) (snd x))›
    and Identity_Elements
    and ‹(⋀i. Functionality (T i) (P i)) ⟹ Functionality (Σ T) (λx. P (fst x) (snd x))›
    and ‹(⋀p. Carrier_Set (T p) (P p)) ⟹ Carrier_Set (Σ T) (λx. P (fst x) (snd x)) › ― ‹Gusser fails to
                    realize the predicate ‹P› can also be parameterized, which is a specific feature of the dependent sum›
    and Abstraction_to_Raw
    and ‹(⋀a c. a ⦂ T c 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 b ⦂ Itself 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 b. r a b c @tag to Itself)
      ⟹ ∀(x::?'b × ?'a). x ⦂ Σ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ Itself 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 y. (∃b. r (snd x) b (fst x) ∧ y = b) @tag to Itself ›

subsubsection ‹Quasi Functor Properties›

text ‹Any non-constantly parameterized φ-types are represented by ‹Σ›. Therefore,
  ‹Σ› is the only parameterized φ-type for which we need to configure its reasoning rules manually.›

text ‹The following properties are nice but essentially useless for reasoning as we have registered
  the intro- and elim-rules for ‹Σ› destructing any ‹Σ› occurring in the reasoning.
  So, the properties below are just listed for aesthetics of math.
›

lemma Σ_pseudo_Transformation_Functor:
  ‹ (⋀a c. a ⦂ T c 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 b ⦂ U c' 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 b c'. g (c,a) (c',b))
⟹ x ⦂ Σ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ Σ U 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 y. g x y ›
  unfolding Transformation_def
  by (cases x; clarsimp; blast)

lemma Σ_pseudo_Functional_Transformation_Functor:
  ‹ snd x ⦂ T (fst x) 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ U c 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 P 
⟹ x ⦂ Σ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 (c,y) ⦂ Σ U 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 P ›
  unfolding Transformation_def
  by (cases x; clarsimp)

lemma Σ_pseudo_Separation_Homo⇩I:
  ‹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 fst (fst x) = fst (snd x)
⟹ x ⦂ Σ T ∗ Σ U 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 (fst (fst x), (snd (fst x), snd (snd x))) ⦂ Σ c. (T c ∗ U c) ›
  unfolding Transformation_def Premise_def
  by clarsimp

lemma Σ_pseudo_Separation_Homo⇩E:
  ‹ x ⦂ Σ c. (T c ∗ U c) 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 ((fst x, fst (snd x)), (fst x, snd (snd x))) ⦂ Σ T ∗ Σ U ›
  unfolding Transformation_def Premise_def
  by clarsimp

lemma Σ_fundef_cong[fundef_cong]:
  ― ‹The rule fails to be derived due to the absence of the standard
      Transformation Functor property›
  ‹ x = y
⟹ (F (fst y) (snd y) = G (fst y) (snd y))
⟹ Σ F x = Σ G y ›
  unfolding φDependent_Sum_def φType_def

subparagraph ‹To-Transformation›

text ‹To-Transformation is still type-directed and the target type ‹U› is inferred according to the
  instruction of the annotation ‹to 𝒯›. In case of ‹Σ›, the thing is ‹to (Σ c. 𝒯 c)› does not fix
  the parameter of ‹𝒯› because the parameter ‹c› is from object, and the parameter cannot be left unknown
  to expect some instantiation in the later reasoning because ‹U› is also unknown having to be inferred,
  causing higher order unknowns ‹U c› which are undecidable and usually not uniquely determined.
  More annotations have to be given from user.
  We invent syntax ‹Σ c. 𝒯 c 𝗉𝖺𝗋𝖺𝗆: f› to annotate the target parameter by a function ‹f› over the
  source object, supporting dynamic choice of the parameter.
›

definition Param_Annot :: ‹'a::{} ⇒ 'p::{} ⇒ 'a::{}› (infix "𝗉𝖺𝗋𝖺𝗆:" 60)
  where ‹x 𝗉𝖺𝗋𝖺𝗆: p ≡ x›

lemma [φreason %To_ToA_cut+20]:
  ‹ WARNING TEXT(‹The parameter of the ‹Σ› type is not annotated. To prevent higher-order unknowns,›
                 ‹we assume the parameter is unchanged throughout the To-Transformation.›)
⟹ PROP Reduce_HO_trivial_variable (Trueprop (
        snd x ⦂ T (fst x) 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 b ⦂ U (fst x) 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 b. g b @tag to (Z (fst x))))
⟹ x ⦂ Σ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ Σ U 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 y. fst y = fst x ∧ g (snd y) @tag to (Σ Z) ›
  unfolding Action_Tag_def Transformation_def Reduce_HO_trivial_variable_def

subsection ‹Nondeterministic Abstraction›

text ‹Transformation functor requires inner elements to be transformed into some fixed φ-type
  independently with the element. It seems to be a limitation. For example, we want to transform
  a list of numbers whose bit-length is unknown ‹l ⦂ List ℕ⇩f⇩r⇩e⇩e› where ‹x ⦂ ℕ⇩f⇩r⇩e⇩e ≡ (x ⦂ ℕ[b] 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 b. x < 2^b)›
  into a set of all lists of such numbers ‹{l | ? } ⦂ List ℕ[?]› where the question marks denote
  the terms cannot be expressed yet now.

  Such transformation can be expressed by ∗‹Dependent Sum Type› ‹Σ› and ∗‹Set Abstraction› ‹LooseState› ›

declare SubjectionTY_def[embed_into_φtype del] ― ‹replaced by ‹Set_Abst››

declare [[φtrace_reasoning = 0]]

φtype_def Set_Abst :: ‹('a,'b) φ ⇒ ('a, 'b set) φ› ("𝒮")
  where [embed_into_φtype]: ‹s ⦂ 𝒮 T ≡ (x ⦂ T 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x. x ∈ s)›
   
 deriving Sep_Functor_1 ― ‹Its Object_Equiv is an example for non-symmetric reachability relation›
      and Abstract_Domain⇩L
      and ‹Transformation_Functor 𝒮 𝒮 T U (λx. x) (λ_. UNIV) (λg Sx Sy. Sy = {y. ∃x∈Sx. g x y})›
      and ‹Functional_Transformation_Functor Set_Abst Set_Abst T U
                     (λx. x) (λ_. UNIV) (λ_ _ _. True) (λf P X. { f x |x. x ∈ X ∧ P x })›
      and ‹Separation_Homo⇩I 𝒮 𝒮 𝒮 T U UNIV (λx. case x of (A, B) ⇒ A × B)›
      and Carrier_Set
      and Open_Abstraction_to_Raw
      and ‹c ⦂ Itself 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 x ⦂ T ⟹ c ⦂ Itself 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 {x} ⦂ 𝒮 T ›
      and ‹(⋀x. x ⦂ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ Itself 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 y. r x y @tag to Itself)
        ⟹ ∀s. (s ⦂ 𝒮 T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ Itself 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 y. (∃x. r x y ∧ x ∈ s) @tag to Itself)›


text ‹Read it as 'the abstract object is certain element in the set'

Together with the \<^const>‹SubjectionTY›, \<^const>‹φDependent_Sum› and \<^const>‹Set_Abst› embed
  BI connective ‹∧› (\<^const>‹Subjection›) and ‹∃› (\<^const>‹ExBI›) into φ-types. The embedding of ‹∃›
  is in an algebraic way having good properties like the Σ-Homomorphism and 𝒮-Homomorphism introduced below.

The system reduces the three φ-types actively just like how it reduces BI ‹∃› and ‹∧›.
Any pure facts in the conjunctions are extracted and stored, and existentially quantified variables are fixed.
This reduction is reversible (meaning loosing no information).

User should define their own φ-types wrapping ‹𝒮› if they do not want this reduction.
However, a specific fixed variable is generally easier to use than a certain element in a set.

‹Σ›-type usually cannot be reduced because there is no non-trivial homomorphism
‹x ⦂ F(Σ T) ⟷ f(x) ⦂ Σ(F T)› that moves a ‹Σ› out from a type operator ‹F›, unless
all the first projection of the elements of ‹x› are equal. However,
the reasoning about ‹Σ› has no problem because the ‹x› is given, so the parameters of the type i.e.,
the first projections of the elements of ‹x› are known.
We can apply ‹Σ⇩E› and ‹Σ⇩I› in the element transformation of ‹x› by ‹F›'s transformation functor property,
and the generated proof obligations about ‹x› are able to specify the type parameter of ‹T›,
e.g., if all the first projection of the elements of ‹x› are unchanged throughout the transformation, the
  type parameter of ‹T› is unchanged).
‹x ⦂ Σ T ⟶ π⇩2(x) ⦂ T (π⇩1 x)     (Σ⇩E)›
‹x ⦂ T(c) ⟶ (c,x) ⦂ Σ T        (Σ⇩I)›

‹𝒮› type has homomorphism, and it is entailed in Transformation Functor.

›

declare SubjectionTY_def[embed_into_φtype add]
        Set_Abst_def[embed_into_φtype del]

lemma Set_Abst_single[embed_into_φtype]:
  ‹{x} ⦂ 𝒮 T ≡ x ⦂ T›
  unfolding atomize_eq BI_eq_iff
  by clarsimp

lemma Set_Abst_unfold_defined:
  ‹ {x. x = y ∧ P} ⦂ 𝒮 T ≡ y ⦂ T 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P ›
  unfolding atomize_eq BI_eq_iff
  by clarsimp

lemma Set_Abst_unfold_Ex:
  ‹ {x. ∃a. P x a} ⦂ 𝒮 T ≡ {x. P x a} ⦂ 𝒮 T 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 a. ⊤ ›
  unfolding atomize_eq BI_eq_iff
  by clarsimp blast

lemma Set_Abst_unfold':
  ‹ NO_MATCH {a} s
⟹ NO_MATCH {x. x = y'∧ P'} s
⟹ NO_MATCH {x. ∃a. P'' x a} s
⟹ (s ⦂ 𝒮 T) = (x ⦂ T 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x. x ∈ s)›
  using Set_Abst.unfold .

  Set_Abst_single
  Set_Abst_unfold_defined
  Set_Abst_unfold_Ex

val BI_Ex_embed_P = Simplifier.make_simproc \<^context> "BI_Ex_embed" {
  lhss = [\<^pattern>‹Collect _ ⦂ 𝒮 _ φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 _›],
  proc = fn _ => fn ctxt => fn ctm =>
    SOME ((Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹ {x. f x} ⦂ 𝒮 T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P ≡ {x. f x ∧ P} ⦂ 𝒮 T ›
                               by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq BI_eq_iff, blast)}
           then_conv Conv.arg1_conv (Conv.arg_conv (Conv.abs_conv (fn (_, ctxt) =>
        let fun conv ctxt =
                        Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹(∃x. Q x) ∧ P ≡ ∃x. Q x ∧ P›
                                            by (unfold atomize_eq, blast)}
              then_conv Conv.arg_conv (Conv.abs_conv (conv o snd) ctxt)
              else_conv Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹(Q ∧ R) ∧ P ≡ Q ∧ R ∧ P›
                                            by (unfold atomize_eq, blast)}
              then_conv Conv.arg_conv (conv ctxt)
              else_conv Conv.all_conv
         in conv ctxt
        end) ctxt))) ctm)
}

val BI_Ex_embed_proc = Simplifier.make_simproc \<^context> "BI_Ex_embed" {
  lhss = [\<^pattern>‹_ ⦂ _ 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x. ⊤›],
  proc = fn _ => fn ctxt => fn ctm =>
    case Thm.term_of ctm
      of Const(\<^const_name>‹ExBI›, _) $ Abs (_, _, Const(\<^const_name>‹φType›, _) $ _ $ T) => (
          case T
            of Const(\<^const_name>‹SubjectionTY›, _) $ T $ P => (
                  case P
                    of Const(\<^const_name>‹Set.member›, _) $ Bound 0 $ _ =>
                        SOME (Conv.rewr_conv
                           (@{print} @{lemma' ‹x ⦂ T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x ∈ s 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x. ⊤ ≡ s ⦂ 𝒮 T› for T s
                                by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq BI_eq_iff) }) ctm)
                     | _ =>
                        if Term.is_dependent T
                        then SOME (Conv.rewr_conv
                                @{lemma' ‹f x ⦂ T x φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P x 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x. ⊤ ≡ { (x, f x) |x. P x } ⦂ 𝒮 (Σ x. T x)› for f T P
                                     by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq BI_eq_iff) } ctm)
                        else SOME (Conv.rewr_conv
                                @{lemma' ‹f x ⦂ T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 P x 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x. ⊤ ≡ { f x |x. P x } ⦂ 𝒮 T› for f T P
                                     by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq BI_eq_iff) } ctm))
             | Const(\<^const_name>‹Set_Abst›, _) $ T => (
                  if Term.is_dependent T
                  then let fun conv ctxt ctmx =
                                  ( Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹ (∃y. EQ y ∧ (∃x. P x y)) ≡ ∃x y. EQ y ∧ P x y › for EQ P
                                                        by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq, blast)}
                          then_conv Conv.arg_conv (Conv.abs_conv (conv o snd) ctxt)
                          else_conv Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹ (∃y. x = (c, y) ∧ y = y' ∧ P y) ≡ x = (c, y') ∧ P y' › for x c P y'
                                                        by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq)}
                          else_conv Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹ (∃y. x = (c, y) ∧ y = y') ≡ x = (c, y') › for x c y'
                                                        by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq)} ) ctmx
                    in SOME ((
                          Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹ {x. P c x} ⦂ 𝒮 (T c) 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 c. ⊤ ≡ {(c, y) |c y. P c y} ⦂ 𝒮 (Σ T) › for P T
                                              by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq BI_eq_iff) }
                          then_conv Conv.arg1_conv (Conv.arg_conv (Conv.abs_conv (fn (_, ctxt) =>
                                        Conv.arg_conv (Conv.abs_conv (conv o snd) ctxt)) ctxt))
                          ) ctm)
                   end
                  else SOME (Conv.rewr_conv
                          @{lemma' ‹ {x. P c x} ⦂ 𝒮 T 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 c. ⊤ ≡ {x. ∃c. P c x} ⦂ 𝒮 T › for P T
                               by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq BI_eq_iff) } ctm))
             | _ => if Term.is_dependent T
                    then SOME (Conv.rewr_conv @{lemma' ‹f x ⦂ T x 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 x. ⊤ ≡ { (x, f x) |x. True } ⦂ 𝒮 (Σ x. T x)› for f T

                                                   by (clarsimp simp: atomize_eq BI_eq_iff)} ctm) 
           )
       | _ => NONE
}

text ‹
  We do not use deriver here.
  It is too basic and our reasoner can barely do little about φ-types embedded in a
  satisfaction statement because it as a pure proposition loses the type structure to guide our
  reasoner. As a consequence, almost every property of the φ-type has to be proven manually.

  For this reason, user should use ‹(T ⨾ U)› instead of a raw satisfaction statement ‹x ⊨ X›.
  The only meaningful interpretation of the satisfaction statement that we can imagine, is for
  vertical composition of abstractions. Therefore, ‹(T ⨾ U)› should be able to replace any usage
  of satisfaction statement.
›

lemma (*The above rule is reversible*)
  ‹ ∀T U. Separation_Homo⇩E ((⨾) B) ((⨾) B) ((⨾) B) T U UNIV (λx. x) ⟹ Object_Sep_Homo⇩E B ›
  unfolding Separation_Homo⇩E_def Object_Sep_Homo⇩E_def Transformation_def

subsection ‹Finite Multiplicative Quantification›
  
text ‹The type parameter ‹T› is not paramterized by the quantified variable. It is not a restriction
  as we have ‹Σ›. Instead, only when ‹T› is not parameterized, ‹✱⇧φ I T› forms a semimodule.›

φtype_def φMul_Quant :: ‹'i set ⇒ ('c::sep_algebra, 'x) φ ⇒ ('c::sep_algebra, 'i ⇒ 'x) φ› ("✱⇧φ⇩0")
  where [embed_into_φtype]: ‹✱⇧φ⇩0 I T = (λx. ✱i∈I. x i ⦂ T)›
  deriving Basic
       and ‹Abstract_Domain T P ⟹ Abstract_Domain (✱⇧φ⇩0 I T) (λx. ∀i ∈ I. P (x i)) ›
       (*and Abstract_Domain⇩L (*TODO*)*)
       and ‹𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 I = J ⟹ Transformation_Functor (✱⇧φ⇩0 I) (✱⇧φ⇩0 J) T U (λx. x ` I) (λ_. UNIV) (λg x y. ∀i∈I. g (x i) (y i))›
       and ‹𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 I = J ⟹ Functional_Transformation_Functor (✱⇧φ⇩0 I) (✱⇧φ⇩0 J) T U (λx. x ` I) (λ_. UNIV) (λ_ P x. ∀i∈I. P (x i)) (λf _. (o) f)›
       and Sep_Functor_1
       and Functionality
       and Module_Assoc
       and Module_One
       and Closed_Module_Zero
       and Carrier_Set

lemma φMul_Quant_induct:
  ‹ 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 finite I
⟹ (⋀T x. P {} T x)
⟹ (⋀I T x i. 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 finite I ⟹ 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 i ∉ I ⟹ P I T x ⟹ P (insert i I) T x)
⟹ P I T x›
  unfolding Premise_def
  subgoal premises prems
    by (insert prems(2-);
        induct rule: finite_induct[OF prems(1)]; clarsimp) .

subsection ‹Sum Type›

lemma pred_sum_is_case_sum[simp]:
  ‹pred_sum = case_sum›
  using pred_sum_eq_case_sum by blast

declare [[φtrace_reasoning = 0]]
 
φtype_def φSum :: ‹('c,'x) φ ⇒ ('c, 'y) φ ⇒ ('c, 'x + 'y) φ› (infixl "+⇩φ" 70)
  where [embed_into_φtype]: ‹(T +⇩φ U) = (λxy. case xy of Inl x ⇒ x ⦂ T | Inr y ⇒ y ⦂ U)›
  deriving ‹Object_Equiv T eq⇩T ⟹ Object_Equiv U eq⇩U ⟹ Object_Equiv (T +⇩φ U) (rel_sum eq⇩T eq⇩U)›
       and Abstract_Domain
       and ‹Abstract_Domain⇩L T T⇩D
        ⟹ Abstract_Domain⇩L U U⇩D
        ⟹ Abstract_Domain⇩L (T +⇩φ U) (case_sum T⇩D U⇩D)› (*simplification fails to transform the result into the ideal form*)
       and ‹Carrier_Set T P
        ⟹ Carrier_Set U Q
        ⟹ Carrier_Set (T +⇩φ U) (pred_sum P Q)› (*simplification fails*)
       and Identity_Elements
       and ‹Identity_Elements⇩E T T⇩D
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩E U U⇩D
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩E (T +⇩φ U) (case_sum T⇩D U⇩D) › (*The inference works, but the result is not in an ideal form,
                                                            so we give the annotation manually*)
       and ‹Identity_Elements⇩I T T⇩D T⇩P
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩I U U⇩D U⇩P 
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩I (T +⇩φ U) (case_sum T⇩D U⇩D) (case_sum T⇩P U⇩P) › (*The inference works*)
       and Functional_Transformation_Functor

lemma [φreason_template name F.φSum⇩E[no_atp]]:
  ‹ Functional_Transformation_Functor F⇩T F T (T +⇩φ U) D⇩T R⇩T pm⇩T fm⇩T
⟹ Functional_Transformation_Functor F⇩U F U (T +⇩φ U) D⇩U R⇩U pm⇩U fm⇩U
⟹ (𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒 D : (λx. case x of Inl u ⇒ (∀a ∈ D⇩T u. Inl a ∈ R⇩T u)
                             | Inr v ⇒ (∀b ∈ D⇩U v. Inr b ∈ R⇩U v))) @tag 𝒜_template_reason undefined
⟹ (𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒 r : (embedded_func (case_sum (fm⇩T Inl (λ_. True)) (fm⇩U Inr (λ_. True)))
                               (pred_sum (pm⇩T Inl (λ_. True)) (pm⇩U Inr (λ_. True))))) @tag 𝒜_template_reason undefined
⟹ Tyops_Commute⇩2⇩_⇩1 F F⇩T F⇩U (+⇩φ) (+⇩φ) T U D r ›
  unfolding Tyops_Commute⇩2⇩_⇩1_def Functional_Transformation_Functor_def Premise_def
            Action_Tag_def Simplify_def
  by (clarify; case_tac x; clarsimp)

lemma [φreason_template name F.φSum⇩I[no_atp]]:
  ‹ Functional_Transformation_Functor F F'⇩T (T +⇩φ U) T D⇩T R⇩T pm⇩T fm⇩T
⟹ Functional_Transformation_Functor F F'⇩U (T +⇩φ U) U D⇩U R⇩U pm⇩U fm⇩U
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 (∀x a. a ∈ D⇩T x ∧ isl a ⟶ projl a ∈ R⇩T x) ∧
           (∀x a. a ∈ D⇩U x ∧ ¬ isl a ⟶ projr a ∈ R⇩U x)
⟹ (𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[φinstantiation] D : (λx. (∀a ∈ D⇩T x. isl a) ∨ (∀b ∈ D⇩U x. ¬ isl b))) @tag 𝒜_template_reason undefined
⟹ (𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[φinstantiation] r : (embedded_func (λx. if (∀a ∈ D⇩T x. isl a)
                                    then Inl (fm⇩T projl (λ_. True) x)
                                    else Inr (fm⇩U projr (λ_. True) x))
                               (λx. if (∀a ∈ D⇩T x. isl a)
                                    then pm⇩T projl (λ_. True) x
                                    else pm⇩U projr (λ_. True) x))) @tag 𝒜_template_reason undefined
⟹ Tyops_Commute⇩1⇩_⇩2 F F'⇩T F'⇩U (+⇩φ) (+⇩φ) T U D r ›
  unfolding Functional_Transformation_Functor_def Tyops_Commute⇩1⇩_⇩2_def Premise_def Simplify_def Action_Tag_def
  apply (clarify; case_tac ‹Ball (D⇩T x) isl›; auto)
  subgoal premises prems for x
    by (insert prems(1)[THEN spec[where x=x], THEN spec[where x=projl], THEN spec[where x=‹λ_. True›]]

  subgoal premises prems for x

               prems(3-),
        clarsimp simp add: Transformation_def split_sum_all Ball_def) .

φtype_def Domainoid ("𝔇[_]" [4] 1000)
    where ‹𝔇[δ] T ≡ δ ⨾⇩f T φ𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 closed_homo_sep δ›
  ― ‹‹Ψ[ψ] (x ⦂ T) ≡ x ⦂ φFun ψ ⨾ T›, therefore ‹φFun ψ ⨾ T› is always an exact solution for
      evaluating ‹Ψ[ψ] (x ⦂ T)›. However, in the case of domainoid extraction, this is not a
      final expression directly giving the domainoids of resources. We want a direct expression
      even if just an upper or lower approximation. Due to this, here
      we introduce a differentiated syntax to emphasize the intention of extracting domainoid,
      on which specific reasoning procedures can be given to reduce the expression further.›
 deriving Sep_Functor
      and Abstract_Domain⇩L
      and ‹ constant_1 δ ∧⇩𝗋 (D,P) = (λ_. True, λ_. True) ∨⇩c⇩u⇩t
            homo_one δ ∧⇩𝗋 Identity_Elements⇩I T D P
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩I (𝔇[δ] T) D P ›

      and ‹ closed_homo_sep δ
        ⟹ constant_1 δ ∧⇩𝗋 Abstract_Domain⇩L T D ∨⇩c⇩u⇩t
            homo_one δ ∧⇩𝗋 Identity_Elements⇩E T D
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩E (𝔇[δ] T) D ›

      and Commutativity_Deriver
      and ‹ comm_domainoid_mapper_rev TYPE('c⇩1::sep_magma) TYPE('c⇩2::sep_magma) δ δ' f f'
        ⟹ Tyops_Commute 𝔇[δ] 𝔇[δ'] ((⨾⇩f) f) ((⨾⇩f) f') T (λx. True) (embedded_func (λx. x) (λ_. True)) ›

      and ‹ comm_domainoid_mapper TYPE('c⇩1::sep_magma) TYPE('c⇩2::sep_magma) δ δ' f f'
        ⟹ Tyops_Commute ((⨾⇩f) f) ((⨾⇩f) f') 𝔇[δ] 𝔇[δ'] T (λx. True) (embedded_func (λx. x) (λ_. True)) ›

subsubsection ‹Application \label{phi-types/Domainoid/App}›
  
lemma [φreason %abstract_domain]:
  ‹ Abstract_Domain⇩L T D⇩T
⟹ Abstract_Domain⇩L U D⇩U
⟹ domainoid TYPE('c::sep_magma) δ
⟹ (⋀x. 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 (closed_homo_sep δ ∧ Satisfiable (x ⦂ T)) ⟹ (f x ⦂ T') ≤ (x ⦂ 𝔇[δ] T))
          ―‹expand ‹Ψ[d] A, Ψ[d] B› to a simpler (but should still strong) upper approximation›
⟹ (⋀y. 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 (closed_homo_sep δ ∧ Satisfiable (y ⦂ U)) ⟹ (g y ⦂ U') ≤ (y ⦂ 𝔇[δ] U))
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 (∀x y. D⇩T x ∧ D⇩U y ⟶ (∃a b. a ⊨ (f x ⦂ T') ∧ b ⊨ (g y ⦂ U') ∧ a ## b))
⟹ Abstract_Domain⇩L (T ∗ U) (λ(x,y). D⇩T x ∧ D⇩U y)›
  unfolding Satisfiable_def BI_sub_iff Premise_def Action_Tag_def domainoid_def domainoid_tag_def
            Abstract_Domain⇩L_def 𝗋ESC_def
  apply (clarsimp simp add: closed_homo_sep_def closed_homo_sep_disj_def)
  by metis

⟹ Functionality T Dx
⟹ Object_Equiv T eq
⟹ Carrier_Set T D⇩C

                            (λs t (x,y). (eq x y ∧ Dx y ∧ D⇩C y ∨ eq y x ∧ Dx x ∧ D⇩C x))
                            (λ_ _. fst) ›
  unfolding Module_Distr_Homo⇩Z_def Transformation_def module_S_distr_def Is_Functional_def
            Object_Equiv_def Functionality_def Abstract_Domain_def Action_Tag_def Satisfiable_def
            scalar_mult_def Carrier_Set_def Within_Carrier_Set_def
  by (clarsimp, metis)

text ‹The domain of abstract objects constrains to ensure the two middle-level objects
  (namely, the concrete objects of ‹T› and the abstract objects of ‹ψ›) are identical so that
  we can apply the right distributive law ‹smult (s + t) a = smult s a * smult t a› of module,
  which requires the group objects ‹a› at the two sides of ‹*› to be identical.

  To this requirement, the instantiated domains above is the weakest.
›

lemma ― ‹The instantiated domains above is the weakest upto using the ‹module_S_distr ψ Ds›,
          i.e., ‹smult (s + t) a = smult s a * smult t a›, when the ‹Dx›, ‹eq›, and ‹D⇩T› are the weakest. ›
  ‹ (∀x. p x ⟷ (∀u v. u ⊨ (x ⦂ T) ∧ v ⊨ (x ⦂ T) ⟶ u = v))
⟹ (∀x y. eq x y ⟷ (x ⦂ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ T))
⟹ (D⇩Tx ⟷ (∃u. u ⊨ (x ⦂ T))) ∧ (D⇩Ty ⟷ (∃u. u ⊨ (y ⦂ T)))
⟹ (∀u v. u ⊨ (x ⦂ T) ∧ v ⊨ (y ⦂ T) ⟶ u = v) ⟶ ((D⇩Tx ⟶ eq x y ∧ p y) ∨ (D⇩Ty ⟶ eq y x ∧ p x)) ›
  unfolding Transformation_def
  by auto metis

  unfolding Module_Distr_Homo⇩S_def Transformation_def module_S_distr_def Is_Functional_def
            Object_Equiv_def Functionality_def Action_Tag_def Satisfiable_def
            scalar_mult_def Carrier_Set_def Within_Carrier_Set_def
  by (clarsimp, metis)

φtype_def φMapTree :: ‹'x set ⇒ ('k,'x) φ ⇒ ('k list ⇒ 'v::one,'y) φ ⇒ ('k list ⇒ 'v, 'x ⇒ 'y) φ›
  where ‹f ⦂ φMapTree D K V ≡ g ⦂ Itself 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 g.
                (∀k. k ∈ D ⟶ pull_map [concretize K k] g ⊨ (f k ⦂ V)) ∧
                g [] = 1 ∧
                (∀k' l. (∀k∈D. k' ≠ concretize K k) ⟶ g (k'#l) = 1 ) ›

  deriving ‹ Object_Equiv V eq
         ⟹ Object_Equiv (φMapTree D K V) (λf g. ∀k∈D. eq (f k) (g k)) ›
    and ‹ Abstract_Domain⇩L K P⇩K ⟹
            Abstract_Domain  V P⇩V ⟹
            Abstract_Domain (φMapTree D K V) (λf. ∀k. P⇩K k ∧ k ∈ D⟶ P⇩V (f k)) ›

text ‹Interesting, relational functor \<^const>‹Transformation_Functor› is (generally) stronger than
  the functional functor \<^const>‹Functional_Transformation_Functor›.
  It is actually the combination of \<^const>‹Functional_Transformation_Functor› and the
  Commutativity of \<^const>‹Set_Abst› over functors. I thought most of functors are also relational
  functors but here, \<^const>‹φMapTree› is an exception.

  \<^term>‹φMapTree D K V› is not relationally functorial over \<^term>‹V› unless (as a suffcient condition)
  \<^term>‹K› is functional. Here is an example demonstrating this.
  Consider a relational transformation
    \<^prop>‹v ⦂ V 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 v' ⦂ V' 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗃 v'. v' ∈ {v⇩1, v⇩2}›
  that non-determistically sends \<^term>‹v ⦂ V› to either \<^term>‹v⇩1 ⦂ V'› or \<^term>‹v⇩2 ⦂ V'›.

  Consider \<^term>‹g ⊨ (f ⦂ φMapTree D K V)› and assume \<^term>‹k ⦂ K› cannot distinguish ‹k⇩1, k⇩2›, i.e.,
  ‹k⇩1 ⊨ (k ⦂ K)›, ‹k⇩2 ⊨ (k ⦂ K)›, both ‹k⇩1,k⇩2› are abstracted to the same abstraction \<^term>‹k›.
  \<^prop>‹g ⊨ (f ⦂ φMapTree D K V)› requires that the \<^term>‹f k ⦂ V› also cannot distinguish ‹g k⇩1, g k⇩2›
  even when they could be different. ‹f k› must be an abstraction of both ‹g k⇩1, g k⇩2›.

  Now, assume the abstraction relation ‹V› is transformed to ‹V'›. Under ‹V'›, ‹g k⇩1, g k⇩2›
  may not keep indistinguishable --- ‹g k⇩1, g k⇩2› may have disjoint abstractions under ‹V'› and may not
  have a common abstraction.

  When ‹v ⦂ V› is transformed to ‹V'›, we could use a set ‹{v⇩1,v⇩2}›
  to non-deterministically specify all possible choices. However, here we cannot similarly use the same
  way because for set ‹S›, any element ‹f ∈ S›, ‹g ⊨ (f ⦂ φMapTree D K V')› always requires
  ‹g k⇩1, g k⇩2› to have a common abstraction ‹f k›, whereas we've said above,
  ‹g k⇩1, g k⇩2› may not have a common abstraction under ‹V'›.
›

lemma Transformation_Functor [φreason add]:
      ‹ Transformation_Functor (φMapTree D K) (φMapTree D K) V V' (λf. f ` D) (λ_. UNIV) (λr f g. ∀k∈D. r (f k) (g k))›
  unfolding Transformation_Functor_def Transformation_def Functionality_def rel_fun_def          
            Abstract_Domain⇩L_def 𝗋ESC_def
  apply (clarsimp simp: Satisfiable_def)
  subgoal premises prems for f g v proof -
    obtain h where t1: ‹a∈D ⟹ v ⊨ (f a ⦂ V) ⟹ v ⊨ (h a v ⦂ V') ∧ g (f a) (h a v)› for a v
      using prems(1) by metis
    show ?thesis
      apply (rule exI[where x=‹λk. h k (pull_map [concretize K k] v)›], auto)
      using prems(2) t1 apply blast
      using prems(2) t1 by blast
  qed .


lemma Functional_Transformation_Functor [φreason add]:
  ‹ Abstract_Domain⇩L K' (λk. k ∈ D')
⟹ Functionality K (λk. k ∈ D)
⟹ 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 finite D'

  unfolding Fun_CV_TrFunctor_def Transformation_def Premise_def
  apply (auto simp: Ball_def)
  apply (smt (verit, del_insts) Abstract_Domain⇩L_def Extact_sufficient_conditions_Iden Functionality_sub Transformation_def bij_betw_def concretize_eq domIff image_eqI option.exhaust_sel option.map_sel ranI)
  by (smt (verit, del_insts) Abstract_Domain⇩L_def Functionality_def Satisfiable_def 𝗋ESC_def bij_betw_iff_bijections concretize_SAT)

lemma Separation_Homo⇩E [φreason add]:
  ‹ Injective_on K D
⟹ Abstract_Domain⇩L K (λx. x ∈ D)
⟹ Separation_Homo⇩E (φMapTree D K) (φMapTree D K) (φMapTree D K) T U UNIV unzip_fun ›
  for T :: ‹'c ⇒ ('b list ⇒ 'd::sep_no_inverse) BI›
  unfolding Separation_Homo⇩E_def Transformation_def
  apply (auto simp: subset_iff)
  subgoal premises prems for z v proof -
    have t1[simp]: ‹k ∈ D ⟹ inv_into D (concretize K) (concretize K k) = k› for k
      by (simp add: concretize_inj prems(1) prems(2) prems(4))
    obtain g1 g2 where t2: ‹k ∈ D ⟹
            pull_map [concretize K k] v = g1 k * g2 k ∧ g2 k ⊨ (snd (z k) ⦂ U) ∧ g1 k ⊨ (fst (z k) ⦂ T) ∧ g1 k ## g2 k › for k
      using prems(3) by metis

    have fuck: ‹(λx. If C (A x) (B x)) = If C A B› for A B C
      by auto

    note domIff[iff del]
    show ?thesis
      apply (rule exI[where x=‹λks. if (∃k. ks ≠ [] ∧ hd ks = concretize K k ∧ k ∈ D)
                                    then g1 (inv_into D (concretize K) (hd ks)) (tl ks)
                                    else v ks ›])
      apply (rule exI[where x=‹λks. if (∃k. ks ≠ [] ∧ hd ks = concretize K k ∧ k ∈ D)
                                    then g2 (inv_into D (concretize K) (hd ks)) (tl ks)
                                    else 1›])
      apply (auto simp: pull_map_def )

      apply (auto simp add: fun_eq_iff times_fun)[1]
      subgoal premises prems for x k proof -
        have t4: ‹ pull_map [concretize K k] v = g1 k * g2 k›
          using prems(3) t2 by blast
        have t5: ‹concretize K k # tl x = x›
          using hd_Cons_tl prems(1) prems(2) by fastforce
          show ?thesis
            by (insert t4, auto simp: pull_map_def fun_eq_iff times_fun, metis t5)
        qed
      apply (subst fuck; auto)[1]
      apply (metis comp_apply domIff option.map_sel snd_conv t1 t2 unzip_option_simps(1))
      apply (subst fuck; auto)[1]
      apply (metis comp_apply domIff option.map_sel option.simps(8) t1 t2 zip_option_prj(1))
      apply (simp add: prems(4))
      using prems(5) apply blast
      using sep_disj_fun_def t2 by force
qed .


lemma Module_Distr_Homo⇩S [φreason add]:
  ‹ Injective_on K D
⟹ Abstract_Domain⇩L K (λx. x ∈ D)
⟹ Module_Distr_Homo⇩S (λD. φMapTree D K V) (λ_. True)
                            (λs t _. s ∩ t = {} ∧ s ⊆ D ∧ t ⊆ D) (λs t f. (f, f)) ›
  for V :: ‹('b list ⇒ 'd::sep_magma_1, 'c option) φ›
  unfolding Module_Distr_Homo⇩S_def Transformation_def
  apply auto
  subgoal premises prems for s t z v proof -
    have t1[simp]: ‹k ∈ D ⟹ inv_into D (concretize K) (concretize K k) = k› for k
      by (meson concretize_inj in_mono inv_into_f_f plus_set_in_iff prems(1) prems(2) prems(4) prems(5) prems(6))
    have fuck: ‹(λx. If C (A x) (B x)) = If C A B› for A B C by auto
    have t2: ‹k ∈ t ⟹ inv_into D (concretize K) (concretize K k) ∈ t› for k
      using prems(5) by force
    have [simp]:
      ‹k ∈ t ⟹ pull_map [concretize K k] (λks. if ks ≠ [] ∧ inv_into D (concretize K) (hd ks) ∈ t then v ks else 1) = pull_map [concretize K k] v › for k
      unfolding pull_map_def fun_eq_iff
      by (auto, insert t2, blast)
    have [simp]:
      ‹k ∈ s ⟹ pull_map [concretize K k] (λks. if ks ≠ [] ∧ inv_into D (concretize K) (hd ks) ∈ s then v ks else 1) = pull_map [concretize K k] v › for k
      unfolding pull_map_def fun_eq_iff
      by (auto, metis prems(4) subsetD t1)

    show ?thesis
      apply (rule exI[where x=‹λks. if (ks ≠ [] ∧ inv_into D (concretize K) (hd ks) ∈ s)
                                    then v ks else 1 ›])
      apply (rule exI[where x=‹λks. if (ks ≠ [] ∧ inv_into D (concretize K) (hd ks) ∈ t)
                                    then v ks else 1 ›])
      apply (auto simp: times_fun fun_eq_iff )
      using prems(3) apply blast
      apply (simp add: prems(7))
      using prems(7) apply auto[1]
      apply (simp add: prems(7))
      apply (metis list.collapse plus_set_in_iff prems(4) prems(7) prems(8) subsetD t1 t2)
      using prems(6) apply force
      apply (metis in_mono plus_set_in_iff prems(4) prems(8) t1)
      using prems(6) apply presburger
      apply (metis Int_iff empty_iff plus_set_in_iff prems(3) prems(8) t2)
      using prems(3) sep_disj_fun_def by fastforce
  qed .

φtype_def φMul_Quant⇩Λ :: ‹'i set ⇒ ('i ⇒ ('c::sep_algebra, 'x) φ) ⇒ ('c::sep_algebra, 'i ⇒ 'x) φ› ("✱⇧φ")
  where ‹x ⦂ ✱⇧φ I T ≡ (i, x i) ⦂ ✱⇩0[i∈I] (Σ T)›
  deriving ‹(⋀p. Object_Equiv (T p) (eq p))
        ⟹ Object_Equiv (✱⇧φ I T) (λx y. ∀i ∈ I. eq i (x i) (y i))›
       and ‹(⋀i. Carrier_Set (T i) (P i)) ⟹ Carrier_Set (✱⇧φ I T) (λx. ∀i ∈ I. P i (x i)) ›
                ― ‹the guesser fails to realize the ‹P› can be parameterized, which is a specific
                    feature of ‹φMul_Quant⇩Λ››
       and ‹(⋀i. Functionality (T i) (P i)) ⟹ Functionality (✱⇧φ I T) (λx. ∀i ∈ I. P i (x i)) ›
       and ‹ (⋀i. Abstract_Domain (T i) (P i))
        ⟹ Abstract_Domain (✱⇧φ I T) (λx. ∀i∈I. P i (x i)) ›  
       and ‹ 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 I = J
        ⟹ Transformation_Functor⇩Λ (✱⇧φ I) (✱⇧φ J) T U (λp x. x ` I) (λ_ _. UNIV) (λg x y. ∀i∈I. g i (x i) (y i)) ›
       and ‹𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 I = J
        ⟹ Functional_Transformation_Functor⇩Λ (✱⇧φ I) (✱⇧φ J) T U (λp x. x ` I) (λ_ _. UNIV)
                                         (λ_ P x. ∀i∈I. P i (x i)) (λf _ x i. f i (x i))›
           ― ‹Gusser is not supported on most of the properties of quantifier φ-types›
       and Sep_Functor_1
       and ‹Separation_Homo⇩Λ⇩I (✱⇧φ I) (✱⇧φ I) (✱⇧φ I) T U UNIV zip_fun›
       and ‹Separation_Homo⇩Λ⇩E (✱⇧φ I) (✱⇧φ I) (✱⇧φ I) T U UNIV unzip_fun›
       and Semimodule_NonAssoc 
       and ‹Module_One⇩I (λI. ✱⇧φ I T) (T i) {i} (λ_. True) (λx _. x) (λ_. True)›
       and ‹Module_One⇩E (λI. ✱⇧φ I T) (T i) {i} (λ_. True) (λf. f i) (λ_. True)›
       and ‹Module_Distr_Homo⇩Z (λI. ✱⇧φ I T) (λ_. True) (λ_ _ _. True) (λ_ D⇩g (f,g). f ⊕⇩f[D⇩g] g)›
       and ‹Module_Distr_Homo⇩S (λI. ✱⇧φ I T) (λ_. True) (λ_ _ _. True) (λ_ _ f. (f ,f))›
       and ‹Module_Zero (λI. ✱⇧φ I T) {}›
       and ‹Closed_Module_Zero (λI. ✱⇧φ I T) {}›

lemma φMul_Quant⇩Λ_cong[cong]:
  ‹ (⋀i. i ∈ I ⟹ T i = U i)
⟹ ✱⇧φ I T = ✱⇧φ I U ›
  by (rule φType_eqI; auto simp: Mul_Quant_def; smt (verit) prod.cong)

                          (λ(x⇩d,x⇩a) (y⇩b,y⇩c). length x⇩d = len_intvl.len d)
                          (map f) (map f⇩c)
                          (λx. map f (take (len_intvl.len b) x) @ map f⇩c (drop (len_intvl.len b) x)) (map f⇩c) ›
  for d :: ‹nat len_intvl›
  unfolding separatable_module_zip_def
  by (clarsimp dest!: dabc_equation__len_intvl_D)


φtype_def φMul_Quant_Tree :: ‹(nat ⇒ 'k) ⇒ nat len_intvl ⇒ ('k list ⇒ 'c, 'a) φ ⇒ ('k list ⇒ 'c::sep_algebra, 'a list) φ › ("✱⇩𝕋")
  where ‹l ⦂ φMul_Quant_Tree f iv T ≡ l ⦂ ✱⇩⟦⇩:⇩⟧⇧φ iv (λi. f i ❙→⇩# T)›
  deriving Sep_Functor_1
       and ‹Abstract_Domain T P
        ⟹ Abstract_Domain (φMul_Quant_Tree f iv T) (λx. length x = len_intvl.len iv ∧ list_all P x) ›
       and ‹Object_Equiv T eq
        ⟹ Object_Equiv (φMul_Quant_Tree f iv T) (list_all2 eq) ›
       and ‹Identity_Elements⇩I T T⇩D T⇩P
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩I (φMul_Quant_Tree f iv T) (list_all T⇩D) (λx. length x = len_intvl.len iv ∧ list_all T⇩P x) ›
       and ‹Identity_Elements⇩E T T⇩D
        ⟹ Identity_Elements⇩E (φMul_Quant_Tree f iv T) (λx. length x = len_intvl.len iv ∧ list_all T⇩D x) ›
       and Semimodule_NonAssoc
       and ‹Module_One⇩I (λiv. φMul_Quant_Tree f iv T) (f j ❙→⇩# T) ⟦j:1⦆ (λ_. True) (λx. [x]) (λ_. True)›
       and ‹Module_One⇩E (λiv. φMul_Quant_Tree f iv T) (f j ❙→⇩# T) ⟦j:1⦆ (λl. length l = 1) hd (λ_. True)›

lemma φMul_Quant_Tree_wrap_module_src[φreason default %φMul_Quant_Tree_wrap_module]:
  ‹ 𝗀𝗎𝖺𝗋𝖽 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 len_intvl.start iv ≤ i ∧ i < len_intvl.start iv + len_intvl.len iv
       ∧⇩𝗋 (𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 y' ! (i - len_intvl.start iv) = fst y
            ⟶ ((fst x, w) ⦂ ks ❙→⇩@ T ✼ W 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ U ✼ R 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 P @tag 𝒯𝒫'))
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 length y' = len_intvl.len iv
         ∧ y' ! (i - len_intvl.start iv) = fst y
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] (j, len, j', len') : (len_intvl.start iv, i - len_intvl.start iv,
                                 i + 1, len_intvl.start iv + len_intvl.len iv - i - 1)
⟹ snd x ⦂ W' 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌
       (w, take len y', drop (len+1) y') ⦂ f i ❙→⇩# W ∗ φMul_Quant_Tree f ⟦j:len⦆ U ∗ φMul_Quant_Tree f ⟦j':len'⦆ U @clean
⟹ x ⦂ (f i # ks) ❙→⇩@ T ✼ W' 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 (y', snd y) ⦂ φMul_Quant_Tree f iv U ✼ f i ❙→⇩# R 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 P @tag 𝒯𝒫' ›
  unfolding Action_Tag_def 𝗋Guard_def Ant_Seq_imp φProd'_def
  ❴ premises _ and Tr and _ and _ and C[]
    note times_list_def[simp]
    note t1 = φMapAt_L.scalar_partial_functor[
          where C⇩W = True and C⇩R = True,
          unfolded Action_Tag_def φProd'_def SE_Has_or_Not_def,
          where t'=‹[]› and s=‹[f i]› and s'=‹[f i]› and FW=‹f i ❙→⇩# W›
                        and FR=‹f i ❙→⇩# R›, simplified,
          OF Tr[THEN mp], unfolded times_list_def append_Cons append_Nil
          φProd_expn' φProd_expn'' times_list_def append_Cons append_Nil append_Nil2] ；
    C t1
  ❵ certified by auto_sledgehammer .
